cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses various stream processing systems, which are designed to handle massive amounts of data. This involves distributed and parallel computing techniques to process data in real-time. 
- cs.DB (Databases): Stream processing systems are used to process data in real-time, which is stored in databases. The paper discusses various open-source and commercial solutions for stream processing, which are used in database applications. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the challenges and solutions related to developing and deploying stream processing systems. This involves software engineering techniques to design and implement these systems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): Stream processing systems require efficient algorithms and data structures to process data in real-time. The paper discusses various algorithms and techniques used in stream processing systems. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): Stream processing systems require efficient networking and internet architecture to process data in real-time. The paper discusses various networking and architecture-related challenges and solutions in stream processing systems.
